]], Canada\n*[[William F. Bell]] (BA) \u2013 mayor of [[Richmond Hill, Ontario]]\n*[[Adam Crooks (politician)|Adam Crooks]] (LL.B.) \u2013 [[Minister of Finance (Ontario)|Treasurer of Ontario]], 1872\u201377, [[List of Ontario Attorneys General|Attorney General of Ontario]], 1871\u201372, Member of the [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario]] for [[Toronto West (provincial electoral district)|Toronto West]], 1871\u201374\n*[[Robert Alexander Harrison]] (B.C.L. 1855, D.C.L. 1859 Trin.) \u2013 [[Member of Parliament (Canada)|Member of Parliament]] for [[West Toronto]], 1867\u201372\n*[[Arthur Matheson]] (B.A. Trin.) \u2013 [[Minister of Finance (Ontario)|Treasurer of Ontario]], 1905\u201313, Member of the [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario]] for [[Lanark South]], 1898\u20131913\n*[[Thomas Moss (jurist)|Thomas Moss]] (B.A. 1858, M.A. 1859) \u2013 [[Member of Parliament (Canada)|Member of Parliament]] for [[West Toronto]], 1873\u201375, [[Chief Justice of Ontario]], 1878\u201380\n*[[James Wellington McLaughlin]] (B.A.) \u2013 Member of the [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario]] for [[Durham West (provincial electoral district)|Durham West]], 1879\u201390\n*[[William Lount]] (LL.B.) \u2013 [[Member of Parliament (Canada)|Member of Parliament]] for [[Toronto Centre]], 1896\u201397, former justice in the Common Pleas division of the [[Supreme Court of Ontario]]\n*[[Thomas Dixon Craig]] (B.A.) \u2013 [[Member of Parliament (Canada)|Member of Parliament]], 1891\u20131900, as an independent [[Conservative Party of Canada (historical)|Conservative]] member\n*[[James Joseph Foy]] (B.A. St.M.) \u2013 [[Attorney General of Ontario]], 1905\u201314, Member of the [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario]] for [[Toronto South (provincial electoral district)|Toronto South]], 1898\u20131916\n*[[Richard Harcourt]] (B.A.) \u2013 [[Minister of Finance (Ontario)|Treasurer of Ontario]], 1890\u201399, Member of the [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario]] for [[Monck (electoral district)|Monck]], 1879\u20131908