]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases|title=Top 40/R Future Releases|accessdate=January 24, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180124203954/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases|archivedate=January 24, 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n* {{sup|{{note|a|[a]}}}} signifies an uncredited co-[[Record producer|producer]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|jay-rock|kings-dead}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n* {{YouTube|3Po4tZ_kfcU|Audio}}\n\n{{Jay Rock}}\n{{Kendrick Lamar songs}}\n{{Future (rapper)}}\n{{James Blake}}\n{{Marvel Cinematic Universe|selected=Music}}\n\n[[Category:2018 songs]]\n[[Category:2018 singles]]\n[[Category:Black Panther (film series)]]\n[[Category:Future (rapper) songs]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award for Best Rap Performance]]\n[[Category:Internet memes introduced in 2018]]\n[[Category:James Blake (musician) songs]]\n[[Category:Jay Rock songs]]\n[[Category:Kendrick Lamar songs]]\n[[Category:Marvel Cinematic Universe music]]\n[[Category:Music memes]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Kendrick Lamar]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Future (rapper)]]\n[[Category:Songs written by 30 Roc]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Jay Rock]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Mike Will Made It]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Sounwave]]\n[[Category:Songs written by James Blake (musician)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 single by Jay Rock, Kendrick Lamar, Future and James Blake}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = King's Dead\n| cover      = Jay Rock, Kendrick Lamar, Future & James Blake - King's Dead.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Jay Rock]], [[Kendrick Lamar]], [[Future (rapper)|Future]] and [[James Blake (musician)|James Blake]]\n| album      = [[Black Panther: The Album]] ''and'' [[Redemption (Jay Rock album)|Redemption]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2018|1|11}}\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   = 2017\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Alternative hip hop]]|[[Trap music|trap]]}}\n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=50}}\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Top Dawg Entertainment|Top Dawg]]|[[Aftermath Entertainment|Aftermath]]|[[Interscope Records|Interscope]]}}\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Kendrick Lamar|Kendrick Duckworth]]|[[Mike Will Made It|Michael Williams]]|[[Teddy Walton|Travis Walton]]|[[Sounwave|Mark Spears]]|[[Jay Rock|Johnny McKinzie]]|[[Future (rapper)|Nayvadius Wilburn]]|[[James Blake (musician)|James Litherland]]|[[30 Roc|Samuel Gloade]]|[[Top Dawg Entertainment|Anthony Tiffith]]|Antwon Hicks|Axel Morgan<ref>https://repertoire.bmi.com/DetailView.aspx?detail=titleid&keyid=26232305&ShowNbr=0&ShowSeqNbr=0&blnWriter=True&blnPublisher=True&blnArtist=True&blnAltTitles=True</ref>}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[Mike Will Made It]]|[[Teddy Walton]]|[[Sounwave]]|[[30 Roc]]{{ref|a|[a]}}|Twon Beatz{{ref|a|[a]}}<ref name=3R>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bd1Q4zwFC15/|title=New Music by @jayrock x @kendricklamar x @future x @jamesblake \"King Dead\" (Prod.By ...|website=[[Instagram]]|accessdate=February 19, 2018}}{{Dead link|date=December 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>|Axlfolie<ref>https://www.grandcruentertainment.com/axlfolie</ref>}}\n| chronology = [[Jay Rock]]\n| prev_title = 90059\n| prev_year  = 2015\n| next_title = Win\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Kendrick Lamar]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = Don't Don't Do It\n | prev_year  = 2018\n | title      = King's Dead\n | year       = 2018\n | next_title = [[Pray for Me (The Weeknd and Kendrick Lamar song)|Pray for Me]]\n | next_year  = 2018\n}}{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Future (rapper)|Future]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Bum Bum Tam Tam#Bum Bum Tam Tam (Remix)|Bum Bum Tam Tam (Remix)]]\n | prev_year  = 2017\n | title      = King's Dead\n | year       = 2018\n | next_title = [[Faded Love (Tinashe song)|Faded Love]]\n | next_year  = 2018\n}}{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[James Blake (musician)|James Blake]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = Vincent\n | prev_year  = 2017\n | title      = King's Dead\n | year       = 2018\n | next_title = [[If the Car Beside You Moves Ahead]]\n | next_year  = 2018\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|VwAnsAUYnw4|\"King's Dead\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''King's Dead'''\" is a song by American rappers [[Jay Rock]], [[Kendrick Lamar]] and [[Future (rapper)|Future]] with British singer [[James Blake (musician)|James Blake]] from the [[Black Panther: The Album|soundtrack album]] of the [[Marvel Studios]] [[superhero film]] ''[[Black Panther (film)|Black Panther]]'' and Jay Rock's third studio album ''[[Redemption (Jay Rock album)|Redemption]]''. It was released by [[Top Dawg Entertainment]], [[Aftermath Entertainment]] and [[Interscope Records]] on January 11, 2018 as both the soundtrack's second single and as the lead single from ''Redemption''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/01/12/577603202/jay-rock-kendrick-lamar-future-james-blake-debut-kings-dead|title=Jay Rock, Kendrick Lamar, Future, James Blake Debut 'King's Dead'|website=[[NPR]]|accessdate=February 2, 2018|date=January 12, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefader.com/2018/01/11/jay-rock-shares-new-song-kings-dead-featuring-kendrick-lamar-future-and-james-blake|title=Jay Rock shares new song \"King's Dead,\" featuring Kendrick Lamar, Future, and James Blake|last=Puckett|first=Lily|website=[[The Fader]]|accessdate=February 3, 2018|date=January 11, 2018}}</ref> The song is Jay Rock's first single to chart on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Zellner|first=Xander|title=Jay Rock Scores First Hot 100 Entry With Kendrick Lamar, Future & James Blake Collab 'King's Dead'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8096084/jay-rock-first-hot-100-entry-kendrick-lamar-future-james-blake-kings-dead|website=Billboard|accessdate=February 2, 2018|date=January 24, 2018}}</ref> The song, along with \"Bubblin\" by [[Anderson Paak]], won [[Grammy Award for Best Rap Performance|Best Rap Performance]], and was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best Rap Song|Best Rap Song]] at the [[61st Annual Grammy Awards]].\n\n==Reception==\nBriana Younger of ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' gave the song a positive review, calling the song \"fun and swaggering\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Younger|first=Briana|title=\"King's Dead\" [ft. Kendrick Lamar, Future, & James Blake] by Jay Rock Review|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/jay-rock-kings-dead-ft-kendrick-lamar-and-future/|website=Pitchfork|date=January 12, 2018|accessdate=February 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video for the song was released to Rock's [[Vevo]] channel on [[YouTube]] on February 15, 2018. It was directed by Dave Free and Jack Begert.<ref>{{cite web|last=William Cowen|first=Trace|title=Here's the Video for Jay Rock, Kendrick Lamar, Future, and James Blake's \"King's Dead\"|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2018/02/jay-rock-kendrick-lamar-future-james-blake-kings-dead-video|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=February 16, 2018|accessdate=February 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Remixes==\nOn March 8, 2018, American rappers [[Joey Badass]] and [[XXXTentacion]] released a remix of the song.<ref>{{citeweb|title=Joey Bada$$ and XXXTentacion link for \"Kings Dead\" remix|url=http://www.elevatormag.com/joey-bada-and-xxxtentacion-link-for-kings-dead-remix/|website=Elevatormag.com|date=March 8, 2018|accessdate=March 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from digital booklet.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/Various-artists-black-panther-the-album-booklet-lyrics|title=Various Artists \u2013 Black Panther: The Album [Booklet]|website=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|accessdate=February 9, 2018|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6x6jb9RKo?url=https://genius.com/Various-artists-black-panther-the-album-booklet-lyrics|archive-date=2018-02-09|url-status=dead}}</ref>{{better source|date=February 2018}}\n\n'''Performers'''\n* [[Jay Rock]] \u2013 vocals\n* [[Kendrick Lamar]] \u2013 vocals\n* [[Future (rapper)|Future]] \u2013 vocals\n* [[James Blake (musician)|James Blake]] \u2013 vocals\n\n'''Technical'''\n* Matt Schaeffer \u2013 record engineering, mix engineering\n* [[Mike Bozzi]] \u2013 master engineering\n* Eric Manco \u2013 record engineering\n\n'''Production'''\n* [[Mike Will Made It]] \u2013 production\n* [[Teddy Walton]] \u2013 production\n* [[Sounwave]] \u2013 additional production\n* [[30 Roc]] \u2013 uncredited co-production\n* {{Proper name|Twon Beatz}} \u2013 uncredited co-production\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/australian-charts-drake-gods-plan-stays-at-no-1-20180224|title=Australian Charts: Drake 'God's Plan' Stays At No 1|publisher=Noise11|last=Ryan|first=Gavin|date=February 24, 2018|accessdate=February 24, 2018}}</ref>\n| 58\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|23|artist=Jay Rock|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 27, 2018}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Greece ([[IFPI Greece]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ifpi.gr/digital_el.html|title=Greece Official IFPI Charts Digital Singles Chart: Feb 5, 2018|work=IFPI Charts|accessdate=March 8, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180206131608/https://www.ifpi.gr/digital_el.html|archive-date=2018-02-06|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| 28\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland3|51|artist=Jay Rock|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 17, 2018}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Netherlands ([[MegaCharts|Single Tip]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dutchcharts.nl/weekchart.asp?cat=st&date=20180224&year=2018|title=Dutchcharts.nl \u2013 Dutch Single Tip \u2013 24/02/2018